## 3. Frontend Architecture (Next.js)

### App Router Structure

```
app/
├── (public)/                   # No auth required
│   ├── page.tsx                # Landing page
│   ├── search/page.tsx         # Teacher discovery (ISR)
│   └── teachers/[slug]/page.tsx # Public teacher profile (SSG+ISR)
│
├── (auth)/                     # Auth pages (no sidebar)
│   ├── login/page.tsx
│   └── onboarding/page.tsx
│
├── (dashboard)/                # Protected — Firebase Auth gate
│   ├── layout.tsx              # Sidebar + Header shell
│   ├── page.tsx                # Dashboard home
│   ├── students/
│   ├── batches/
│   ├── attendance/
│   ├── fees/
│   ├── notes/
│   ├── tests/
│   ├── reports/
│   └── announcements/
│
└── api/                        # API proxies + Next.js edge middleware
    └── v1/[...path]/route.ts   # Proxy to Node.js backend
```

### Rendering Strategy

| Route | Strategy | Why |
|-------|----------|-----|
| `/` | Static | Marketing, infrequent changes |
| `/search` | ISR (1hr) | SEO + fresh data |
| `/teachers/[slug]` | ISR (15min) | SEO critical, changes infrequently |
| `/dashboard/*` | CSR (client hydrated) | Private data, auth-gated |
| `/dashboard/reports` | SSR | Fresh aggregated data on request |

### State Management

```
Client State (Zustand):
  - UI state (sidebar open/closed, modals)
  - Current teacher context
  - Selected batch / filters

Server State (TanStack Query):
  - All API data (students, batches, fees...)
  - Automatic background refetch
  - Optimistic updates for mutations (e.g., mark paid)

Auth State (Firebase Auth SDK):
  - onAuthStateChanged listener
  - Token stored in cookie (for SSR hydration)
```

---

## 4. Backend Modules (Node.js)

### Module Structure Pattern

Each module follows the same folder layout:

```
modules/
└── students/
    ├── students.router.ts      # Express routes
    ├── students.controller.ts  # Request parsing, response shaping
    ├── students.service.ts     # Business logic
    ├── students.repository.ts  # Firestore data access
    ├── students.schema.ts      # Zod validation schemas
    └── students.types.ts       # TypeScript interfaces
```

### Module: Teachers
```
Routes:
  POST   /teachers/              → Create teacher profile (post-auth)
  GET    /teachers/:id           → Get teacher profile
  PATCH  /teachers/:id           → Update profile
  GET    /teachers/:id/dashboard → Dashboard summary (cached)
  GET    /teachers/slug/:slug    → Public profile by slug

Service:
  - Profile CRUD
  - Dashboard KPI aggregation (students count, fees due, today's batches)
  - Public profile slug generation
  - Verification status management
```

### Module: Students
```
Routes:
  GET    /students              → List all students (with filters)
  POST   /students              → Add single student
  POST   /students/bulk         → Bulk import via CSV
  GET    /students/:id          → Student profile + batch history
  PATCH  /students/:id          → Update student
  DELETE /students/:id          → Soft-delete (archive)

Service:
  - Student CRUD
  - CSV parsing and validation
  - Batch enrollment history query
  - Fee status aggregation per student
```

### Module: Batches
```
Routes:
  GET    /batches               → List batches (active/all)
  POST   /batches               → Create batch
  GET    /batches/:id           → Batch detail + enrolled students
  PATCH  /batches/:id           → Update batch
  POST   /batches/:id/students  → Assign/unassign students
  POST   /batches/:id/clone     → Clone batch for new term

Service:
  - Batch CRUD
  - Student enrollment management (many-to-many via enrollments collection)
  - Schedule conflict detection
  - Seat count tracking (denormalized counter)
```

### Module: Attendance
```
Routes:
  GET    /attendance/:batchId         → Get attendance for date range
  POST   /attendance/:batchId         → Mark attendance for a date
  PATCH  /attendance/:batchId/:date   → Update attendance (retroactive)
  GET    /attendance/student/:id      → Per-student attendance stats

Service:
  - Attendance write (upsert per batch+date)
  - Holiday management
  - Attendance % calculation (present / (total - holidays))
  - Monthly summary aggregation (cached in Redis)
```

### Module: Fees
```
Routes:
  GET    /fees/:batchId              → Fee overview for batch
  POST   /fees/generate              → Generate fee records for batch
  POST   /fees/:recordId/pay         → Mark student as paid
  POST   /fees/:recordId/partial     → Record partial payment
  GET    /fees/student/:studentId    → Full fee history for student
  GET    /fees/report                → Dues / collection report

Service:
  - Fee record generation (bulk create per batch)
  - Payment recording (cash / UPI / cheque modes)
  - Partial payment & balance tracking
  - Overdue detection (past due date, unpaid)
  - Monthly collection totals
```

### Module: Notes
```
Routes:
  GET    /notes              → List notes (by batch or all)
  POST   /notes              → Upload note metadata (after Firebase Storage upload)
  DELETE /notes/:id          → Delete note + cleanup storage

Service:
  - Signed URL generation for Firebase Storage uploads
  - Note metadata CRUD in Firestore
  - Batch-scoped or teacher-global notes
```

### Module: Reports
```
Routes:
  GET    /reports/attendance  → Attendance report (date range, batch filter)
  GET    /reports/fees        → Fee collection report
  GET    /reports/tests       → Test performance report
  GET    /reports/students    → Per-student combined report

Service:
  - Aggregation queries across multiple collections
  - CSV/PDF export (using pdfkit / fast-csv)
  - Caching heavy aggregations in Redis (TTL: 1 hour)
```

### Module: Announcements
```
Routes:
  GET    /announcements          → List announcements
  POST   /announcements          → Create + send announcement
  PATCH  /announcements/:id/pin  → Pin/unpin

Service:
  - Announcement CRUD
  - WhatsApp message link generation (wa.me/91{phone}?text=...)
  - Batch-targeted or all-students targeting
  - Scheduled announcements (Bull queue / Firestore scheduled functions)
```

